Rating: 4
Superb. My catering co-worker had a party and he asked me to prepare these. For that little something extra I brined the drumettes in 1/2 salt 1/2 brown sugar solution. The guest and I were delighted with the outcome. I like the sauce thick so I boiled it down quite a bit. This is a keeper.

Rating: 2
I certainly thought this was good, but not out of this world (although in the recipe's defense I used dried Bing cherries rather than sour cherries). The recipe was not at all difficult and the directions were very accurate. I would not discourage anyone from trying this, since it seemed to please so many other reviewers, but I doubt I'll make it again. I'm really more into thinner, vinegar-based barbecue sauces. I'm wild for sauce from the "Chicken with Sweet and Spicy Barbecue Sauce" from the Epicurious site; consider trying that one!

